          <div class="sp-faqx-panel active" data-cat="problems" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Do you install both natural and manufactured stone veneers?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Yes. While natural stone provides unparalleled luxury, we also expertly install high-end manufactured veneers. We advise builders on the best material weight and profile for the specific architectural intent.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">How do you ensure the veneer looks like solid masonry?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Through artisanal corner treatments and randomized face setting. We meticulously weave corner pieces so that the facade mimics the depth and structural gravity of full-thickness brick or stone.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="cost" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">How do you prevent water from getting trapped behind the stone?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">We construct a sophisticated rain screen system utilizing dual-layer barriers and strategically placed weep screeds. This allows any condensation to safely exit, permanently protecting the timber framing from rot.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Does veneer require different mortar than traditional brick?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Absolutely. We utilize specialized polymer-modified mortars for the scratch coat and setting bed to achieve maximum sheer bond strength, preventing the heavier stone units from sagging or delaminating.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="repair" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">How do you integrate with our framing and siding crews?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">We communicate proactively with the GC to sequence our lath and scratch coat application perfectly alongside window installation and siding crews, ensuring seamless flashed transitions.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Can you provide detailed material takeoffs from plans?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Yes, our estimating team provides exact square footage and corner linear footage takeoffs from your blueprints, guaranteeing precise material ordering and waste reduction.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="process" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Who oversees the veneer installation on site?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Every project is managed directly by an AMS foreman who is a full-time employee. The company owners are also regularly on site verifying adherence to our stringent quality control metrics.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
